    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your chicken out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Turn on your <strong>slow cooker</strong> to high</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-tamarind-and-coconut-chicken-curry/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green</strong> <strong>beans</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-tamarind-and-coconut-chicken-curry/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken </strong>to the <strong>slow cooker</strong> with the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-tamarind-and-coconut-chicken-curry/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tamarind & coconut curry paste</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, stir it all together and cook on high for an initial 2 hours</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-tamarind-and-coconut-chicken-curry/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 2 hours, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>chopped green beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-tamarind-and-coconut-chicken-curry/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for a further 2 hours or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>tamarind & coconut chicken curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the curry is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-tamarind-and-coconut-chicken-curry/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the curry has 15 min left, add your <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-tamarind-and-coconut-chicken-curry/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>slow cooker</strong> <strong>tamarind & coconut chicken curry </strong>with the<strong> cooked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
